Step 1: 
Download jira: Jira Software at https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/download
wget https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/downloads/binary/atlassian-jira-software-7.8.2-x64.bin

Step 2: Run Installer , make it executable: 
$ chmod a+x atlassian-jira-software-X.X.X-x64.bin
$ sudo chmod a+x atlassian-jira-software-7.8.2-x64.bin


Step 3: Run installer , create a dedicated account to run jira 
$ sudo ./atlassian-jira-software-X.X.X-x64.bin
$ sudo ./atlassian-jira-software-7.8.2-x64.bin
press enter key when prompt

Step 4: 
At next screen choose- Custom Install (recommended for advanced users) [2, Enter]
Choose JIRA installation directory - Enter to choose default path - [/opt/atlassian/jira]
Press Enter (Default location for JIRA Software data)
Type 1  and press enter key to choose default port (HTTP: 8080, Control: 8005)
Type y and hit enter (To start Jira service when system restart)
Type i to install Jira as service
Press y to start JIRA instance

Step 5: JIRA installation done successfully. Let's access JIRA instance after finding ip through ipconfig as shown below
http://192.168.102.10:8080
